<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" style="color-scheme: light">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title @text="title" webc:keep></title>

    <script @raw="`const API_BASE = '${site.apiBase}';`" webc:keep>
      const FETCH_OPTS = { credentials: "include" };
    </script>

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/vendor/maplibre-gl.css" webc:keep />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css" webc:keep />
    <style @raw="getBundle('css')" webc:keep></style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <page-header
      :login-href="page.url === '/' ? '#login' : '/login'"
    ></page-header>
    <msg-banner>
      <span slot="summary">
        <svg
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          width="24"
          height="24"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-linejoin="round"
          stroke-width="2"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        >
          <path stroke="none" d="M0 0h24v24H0z" />
          <path
            d="M12 9v4M10.363 3.591 2.257 17.125a1.914 1.914 0 0 0 1.636 2.871h16.214a1.914 1.914 0 0 0 1.636-2.87L13.637 3.59a1.914 1.914 0 0 0-3.274 0M12 16h.01"
          />
        </svg>
        <strong
          >This is a work-in-progress. Functionality is limited and things will
          be broken.</strong
        ></span
      >
      <div slot="message">
        <div class="g-max-7">
          <p>
            If you’re seeing this, you’re here early.
            <strong>Thank you</strong> for trying things out. I’m building this
            in public and appreciate any and all feedback. With that, there are
            two main things I ask you to keep in mind.
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              Any activities you create are public to the world via a PDS. This
              is because all data on ATProto is public. Activities contain
              location data, which could be sensitive.
              <strong
                >If you don’t want your location data made public, do not create
                activities yet.</strong
              >
              Permissioned/private data is a big topic of conversation in
              ATProto, but as far as I know, there’s no ETA for when it will be
              a thing.
            </li>
            <li>
              Consider this “alpha” software. There’s not much in the way of
              functionality, you will find bugs, and I will most likely bring
              the site down a few times while building.
            </li>
          </ol>
          <p>
            If you have questions, feature requests, or are interested in
            helping out, use any of these:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/thedistance.app">
                @thedistance.app
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="mailto:hello@thedistance.app">hello@thedistance.app </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/tylergaw.com">
                @tylergaw.com
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>–Tyler</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </msg-banner>
    <main @raw="content"></main>
    <page-footer></page-footer>

    <script src="/vendor/maplibre-gl.js" webc:keep></script>
    <script src="/app.js" webc:keep></script>
    <script @raw="getBundle('js', 'components')" webc:keep></script>
  </body>
</html>
